<item>
            <title>[DERBY-6600] Make the Lucene plugin use the database class path to resolve ANALYZERMAKERs and QUERYPARSERMAKERs</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-6600</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;You get a ClassNotFoundException if you try to use an Analyzer or a QueryParser stored in a jar file in the database. This is probably easy to fix: the class resolution needs to use the database class loader.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12718366">DERBY-6600</key>
            <summary>Make the Lucene plugin use the database class path to resolve ANALYZERMAKERs and QUERYPARSERMAKERs</summary>
